-- Sweden's Skanska says Q2 profit hit by Latin American operations
-- 
-- Thu Jul 10, 2014 02:27AM EDT
-- None



STOCKHOLM, July 10 (Reuters) - Construction firm Skanska <SKAb.ST> said on Thursday its second quarter operating profit was expected at 920 million Swedish crowns ($135.53 million), as its Latin American operations showed continued losses.

The company said it was to take a charge of 500 million crowns in Latin America in the quarter.